<TITLE> DU sees new pro-VC, treasurer </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 22 (bdnews24.com) - Dean of social sciences Prof Harun-ur-Rashid has been appointed pro-vice chancellor of Dhaka University, to replace Prof Yusuf Haider, an official of the president's office said Thursday. Prof Mizanur Rahman of the marketing department has been appointed treasurer replacing Prof Syed Abul Kalam Azad, the president's secretary Md Shirajul Islam told bdnews24.com on Thursday. He said the president, also the chancellor of the university, had signed their appointment papers. Prof Harun, of the political science department, said he recieved a faxed circular sent by the education ministry appointing him pro-VC for a four-year term. Newly named treasurer Prof Rahman was appointed following Prof Azad's resignation although he had one more year to go of his term. With the new postings, the country's leading public university has seen new appointments of pro-Awami League teachers in all three top chairs since the AL-led government took office in early january. Journalism professor AAMS Arefin Siddique was appointed vice-chancellor of the university on Jan. 15, after Prof SMA Faiz resigned. bdnews24.
